A 12-year-old boy, Abdulkareem Mu’azu, had allegedly defiled four brothers at Sabon Gari quarters in Kiyawa Local Government Area of Jigawa State. The incident triggered when the Mother of the victim discovered some changes and abnormalities in one of her 8-year-old child. She said after examining the victim, he narrated to her what transpired between him and one of the suspects aged 12 years when they were playing. Spokesman of the Nigeria Security And Civil Defence Corps, Jigawa State command, SC, Adamu Shehu, confirmed the incident to DAILY POST. He said the incident happened on Tuesday, 30th of June, 2020 at about 1830hrs following a complaint lodged by the mother of the victims. Adamu said operatives thereafter invited the suspect for interrogation where he confirmed having canal knowledge of the 8-year-old boy, his brother of 10 years and two others aged 9 and 8 respectively who happened to be family friends. He said medical reports indicated that there is forceful entry and bruises at the anal area of the victim. The suspect further revealed that he was introduced to the act from two other older friends of Mustapha Jafar, 18 years and 17-year-old Abubakar Sule of the same quarters. The NSCDC, however, stated that the two suspects were also arrested and confessed to having canal knowledge of the 12-year-old suspect several times in different locations. He said investigation is still ongoing, and the suspects will be taken to a court of competent jurisdiction for prosecution. The State NSCDC commandant, Alhaji Garba Muhammad, advised parents to be extra vigilant on their children’s movements and those of their associates to avert a similar occurrence.